{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":502,"text":"You may want to take a closer look."},{"time":2708,"text":"There's more to this painting than meets the eye."},{"time":5942,"text":"And yes, it's an acrylic painting of a man,"},{"time":9932,"text":"but I didn't paint it on canvas."},{"time":12364,"text":"I painted it directly on top of the man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15652,"text":"What I do in my art is I skip the canvas altogether,"},{"time":18386,"text":"and if I want to paint your portrait,"},{"time":20252,"text":"I'm painting it on you, physically on you."},{"time":23892,"text":"That also means you're probably going to end up"},{"time":25645,"text":"with an earful of paint,"},{"time":27553,"text":"because I need to paint your ear on your ear."},{"time":31636,"text":"Everything in this scene, the person, the clothes,"},{"time":34252,"text":"chairs, wall, gets covered in a mask of paint"},{"time":37925,"text":"that mimics what's directly below it,"},{"time":40686,"text":"and in this way, I'm able to take a three-dimensional scene"},{"time":44400,"text":"and make it look like a two-dimensional painting."},{"time":47621,"text":"I can photograph it from any angle,"},{"time":49819,"text":"and it will still look 2D."},{"time":52842,"text":"There's no Photoshop here."},{"time":55855,"text":"This is just a photo"},{"time":57617,"text":"of one of my three-dimensional paintings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61288,"text":"You might be wondering how I came up with this idea"},{"time":63408,"text":"of turning people into paintings."},{"time":65672,"text":"But originally, this had nothing to do"},{"time":68466,"text":"with either people or paint."},{"time":70680,"text":"It was about shadows."},{"time":73072,"text":"I was fascinated with the absence of light,"},{"time":75692,"text":"and I wanted to find a way that I could give it materiality"},{"time":79143,"text":"and pin it down before it changed."},{"time":81876,"text":"I came up with the idea of painting shadows."},{"time":84401,"text":"I loved that I could hide within this shadow"},{"time":86592,"text":"my own painted version,"},{"time":88696,"text":"and it would be almost invisible"},{"time":91133,"text":"until the light changed, and all of a sudden"},{"time":93656,"text":"my shadow would be brought to the light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96817,"text":"I wanted to think about what else I could put shadows on,"},{"time":99880,"text":"and I thought of my friend Bernie."},{"time":102160,"text":"But I didn't just want to paint the shadows."},{"time":105390,"text":"I also wanted to paint the highlights"},{"time":107296,"text":"and create a mapping on his body in greyscale."},{"time":110586,"text":"I had a very specific vision of what this would look like,"},{"time":114307,"text":"and as I was painting him,"},{"time":116480,"text":"I made sure to follow that very closely."},{"time":118999,"text":"But something kept on flickering before my eyes."},{"time":121880,"text":"I wasn't quite sure what I was looking at."},{"time":123960,"text":"And then when I took that moment to take a step back,"},{"time":127566,"text":"magic."},{"time":129242,"text":"I had turned my friend into a painting."},{"time":132952,"text":"I couldn't have foreseen that"},{"time":133940,"text":"when I wanted to paint a shadow,"},{"time":136495,"text":"I would pull out this whole other dimension,"},{"time":138389,"text":"that I would collapse it,"},{"time":139747,"text":"that I would take a painting and make it my friend"},{"time":144272,"text":"and then bring him back to a painting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147706,"text":"I was a little conflicted though,"},{"time":149798,"text":"because I was so excited about what I'd found,"},{"time":153120,"text":"but I was just about to graduate from college"},{"time":155424,"text":"with a degree in political science,"},{"time":157200,"text":"and I'd always had this dream"},{"time":159734,"text":"of going to Washington, D.C.,"},{"time":161960,"text":"and sitting at a desk"},{"time":164202,"text":"and working in government."},{"time":166920,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":168968,"text":"Why did this have to get in the way of all that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172168,"text":"I made the tough decision"},{"time":173746,"text":"of going home after graduation"},{"time":177158,"text":"and not going up to Capitol Hill,"},{"time":180258,"text":"but going down to my parents' basement"},{"time":182400,"text":"and making it my job to learn how to paint."},{"time":185870,"text":"I had no idea where to begin."},{"time":189182,"text":"The last time I'd painted,"},{"time":190727,"text":"I was 16 years old at summer camp,"},{"time":193166,"text":"and I didn't want to teach myself how to paint"},{"time":195614,"text":"by copying the old masters"},{"time":197853,"text":"or stretching a canvas"},{"time":199199,"text":"and practicing over and over again on that surface,"},{"time":202576,"text":"because that's not what this project was about for me."},{"time":205380,"text":"It was about space and light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208482,"text":"My early canvases ended up being"},{"time":211325,"text":"things that you wouldn't expect to be used as canvas,"},{"time":214602,"text":"like fried food."},{"time":216760,"text":"It's nearly impossible"},{"time":218884,"text":"to get paint to stick to the grease in an egg."},{"time":221670,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":223746,"text":"Even harder was getting paint to stick"},{"time":226228,"text":"to the acid in a grapefruit."},{"time":228494,"text":"It just would erase my brush strokes"},{"time":231606,"text":"like invisible ink."},{"time":233037,"text":"I'd put something down, and instantly it would be gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236681,"text":"And if I wanted to paint on people,"},{"time":238783,"text":"well, I was a little bit embarrassed"},{"time":241519,"text":"to bring people down into my studio"},{"time":243327,"text":"and show them that I spent my days in a basement"},{"time":246387,"text":"putting paint on toast."},{"time":249523,"text":"It just seemed like it made more sense"},{"time":251382,"text":"to practice by painting on myself."},{"time":254611,"text":"One of my favorite models actually ended up being"},{"time":257537,"text":"a retired old man"},{"time":259321,"text":"who not only didn't mind sitting still"},{"time":261600,"text":"and getting the paint in his ears,"},{"time":264149,"text":"but he also didn't really have much embarrassment"},{"time":266798,"text":"about being taken out into very public places"},{"time":268789,"text":"for exhibition,"},{"time":270401,"text":"like the Metro."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273720,"text":"I was having so much fun with this process."},{"time":277447,"text":"I was teaching myself how to paint in all these different styles,"},{"time":281691,"text":"and I wanted to see what else I could do with it."},{"time":284856,"text":"I came together with a collaborator, Sheila Vand,"},{"time":287813,"text":"and we had the idea of creating paintings"},{"time":290121,"text":"in a more unusual surface,"},{"time":292838,"text":"and that was milk."},{"time":295795,"text":"We got a pool. We filled it with milk."},{"time":298214,"text":"We filled it with Sheila. And I began painting."},{"time":301190,"text":"And the images were always"},{"time":303199,"text":"completely unexpected in the end,"},{"time":305383,"text":"because I could have a very specific image"},{"time":308127,"text":"about how it would turn out,"},{"time":309450,"text":"I could paint it to match that,"},{"time":311706,"text":"but the moment that Sheila laid back into the milk,"},{"time":314272,"text":"everything would change."},{"time":316118,"text":"It was in constant flux,"},{"time":318134,"text":"and we had to, rather than fight it, embrace it,"},{"time":321401,"text":"see where the milk would take us"},{"time":322645,"text":"and compensate to make it even better."},{"time":326789,"text":"Sometimes, when Sheila would lay down in the milk,"},{"time":330047,"text":"it would wash all the paint off of her arms,"},{"time":332641,"text":"and it might seem a little bit clumsy,"},{"time":335795,"text":"but our solution would be, okay, hide your arms."},{"time":338865,"text":"And one time, she got so much milk in her hair"},{"time":341923,"text":"that it just smeared all the paint off of her face."},{"time":344801,"text":"All right, well, hide your face."},{"time":347076,"text":"And we ended up with something far more elegant"},{"time":350487,"text":"than we could have imagined,"},{"time":352332,"text":"even though this is essentially the same solution"},{"time":354547,"text":"that a frustrated kid uses when he can't draw hands,"},{"time":357918,"text":"just hiding them in the pockets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361075,"text":"When we started out on the milk project,"},{"time":363609,"text":"and when I started out,"},{"time":365139,"text":"I couldn't have foreseen that I would go"},{"time":368043,"text":"from pursuing my dream in politics"},{"time":370444,"text":"and working at a desk"},{"time":372145,"text":"to tripping over a shadow"},{"time":373911,"text":"and then turning people into paintings"},{"time":376979,"text":"and painting on people in a pool of milk."},{"time":380259,"text":"But then again, I guess it's also not unforeseeable"},{"time":383667,"text":"that you can find the strange in the familiar,"},{"time":386691,"text":"as long as you're willing to look beyond"},{"time":388196,"text":"what's already been brought to light,"},{"time":389767,"text":"that you can see what's below the surface,"},{"time":392014,"text":"hiding in the shadows,"},{"time":394005,"text":"and recognize that there can be more there"},{"time":396699,"text":"than meets the eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398571,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399944,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}